<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=10483'><h3>View taxon page for Cardamine</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#MN1'">1.</a><a name="MN1."> </a> At least some cauline leaves simple or 0

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#MN2'">2.</a><a name="MN2."> </a> Caudex distinct; rhizomes 0; cauline leaves 0 or 1(2) <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17124">.....&nbsp;C. bellidifolia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#MN2.">2'</a><a name="MN2'"> </a> Caudex 0; rhizomes present; cauline leaves 2&ndash;23

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN3'">3.</a><a name="MN3."> </a> Rhizome not fleshy, 1&ndash;3 mm wide; rhizome leaves generally 0 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17142">.....&nbsp;C. cordifolia</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN3.">3'</a><a name="MN3'"> </a> Rhizome fleshy, (3)4&ndash;18 mm wide; rhizome leaves present

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN4'">4.</a><a name="MN4."> </a> Petals white or pale rose, 8&ndash;13(15) mm; seeds 12&ndash;22; stem (2)2.7&ndash;6(7) dm; leaflets of rhizome leaves (0)3(5&ndash;7) <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=76456">.....&nbsp;C. californica</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN4.">4'</a><a name="MN4'"> </a> Petals pink to purple (white), 14&ndash;18 mm; seeds 10&ndash;14; stem 1&ndash;3 dm; rhizome leaves simple <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=76464">.....&nbsp;C. pachystigma</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#MN1.">1'</a><a name="MN1'"> </a> Cauline leaves pinnately or palmately compound; leaflets 3&ndash;25, occasionally pinnately divided, appearing compound

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#MN5'">5.</a><a name="MN5."> </a> Annual or biennial; rhizomes 0

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN6'">6.</a><a name="MN6."> </a> Basal leaves not rosetted, early-deciduous <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17179">.....&nbsp;C. pensylvanica</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN6.">6'</a><a name="MN6'"> </a> Basal leaves rosetted, persistent

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN7'">7.</a><a name="MN7."> </a> Stamens 4(6); pedicels erect to ascending; fruit generally appressed, glabrous; seeds margined <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17158">.....&nbsp;C. hirsuta</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN7.">7'</a><a name="MN7'"> </a> Stamens 6; pedicels ascending to spreading; fruit generally not appressed, sparsely hairy or glabrous; seeds not margined <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17171">.....&nbsp;C. oligosperma</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#MN5.">5'</a><a name="MN5'"> </a> Perennial herb; rhizomed

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN8'">8.</a><a name="MN8."> </a> Rhizome not fleshy, cylindric

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN9'">9.</a><a name="MN9."> </a> Rhizome leaves present; seeds 6&ndash;16(24) <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17120">.....&nbsp;C. angulata</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN9.">9'</a><a name="MN9'"> </a> Rhizome leaves 0; seeds 14&ndash;28 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17125">.....&nbsp;C. breweri</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#MN8.">8'</a><a name="MN8'"> </a> Rhizome fleshy, segments fusiform, ovoid to oblong or spheric

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN10'">10.</a><a name="MN10."> </a> Leaflets of cauline leaves 5&ndash;7; sepals 1.7&ndash;2 mm; petals 4&ndash;6 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17170">.....&nbsp;C. occidentalis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#MN10.">10'</a><a name="MN10'"> </a> Leaflets of cauline leaves 3(5); sepals 3.5&ndash;5.5 mm; petals 8&ndash;15 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#MN11'">11.</a><a name="MN11."> </a> Cauline leaves 2&ndash;5; stem (2)2.7&ndash;6(7) dm; seeds 12&ndash;22; petals white or pale rose <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=76456">.....&nbsp;C. californica</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#MN11.">11'</a><a name="MN11'"> </a> Cauline leaves 1&ndash;3; stem 0.5&ndash;2(3) dm; seeds 8&ndash;16; petals pale pink to purple (white) <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=17168">.....&nbsp;C. nuttallii</a></blockquote><P>
